# __SKILL_TITLE__

## Overview

This is a managed OpenClaw skill scaffold generated by `openclaw-skill-creator-v1`.

Keep the main body concise and operational.
Move detail into `references/`.

## Portable core to keep

- Keep `name` and `description` as the portable trigger surface.
- Make `description` say what the skill does and when it should trigger.
- Keep runtime-agnostic instructions here.

## OpenClaw-specific profile

- Treat `metadata.openclaw.*` as runtime profile data, not as portable core.
- Document bridge, write, network, and dependency boundaries explicitly.
- Prefer absolute bridge paths when bridge commands are part of the workflow.

## Do not copy these patterns literally

- Do not assume Anthropic-specific packaging or auth behavior.
- Do not assume Codex `agents/openai.yaml` metadata is part of the OpenClaw baseline.
- Do not treat a validator pass as readiness proof.

## Workflow

1. Define the concrete examples this skill should handle.
2. Keep the portable trigger surface short and clear.
3. Put runtime-specific details under the OpenClaw profile.
4. Add deterministic helpers only when they reduce fragility.
5. Prepare real baseline-vs-with-skill evals before claiming readiness.

## Validation

- Run the required tree check.
- Run the lifecycle validator.
- Use isolated managed profiles for eval.
- Apply readiness gates to completed review files.

